{"title_page": "Preservation and Long-term Access through Networked Services", "text_new": "{{short description|Digital preservation project}}\n{{Primary sources|Companies|date=April 2020}}\nThe '''Preservation and Long-term Access through Networked Services''' (PLANETS) project  addressed core digital preservation challenges. The primary goal for Planets was to build practical services and tools to help ensure long-term access to digital cultural and scientific assets. The outputs of this [[Framework_Programmes_for_Research_and_Technological_Development#FP6_and_FP7|European Sixth Framework Programme]] are, since 2010, sustained by the follow-on organisation, the Open Planets Foundation.<ref>{{cite web|title=Planets - Preservation and Long-term Access to our Cultural and Scientific Heritage. Fact Sheet (Record number:99184)|url=https://cordis.europa.eu/project/id/033789|website=cordis.europa.eu|language=en|date=11 April 2016|access-date=7 April 2020|publication-date=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title= Planets project |work= web site |year= 2009 |url= http://www.planets-project.eu/ |accessdate=7 December 2011 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title= The Open Planets Foundation |work= web site |year= 2010 |url= http://www.openplanetsfoundation.org/ |accessdate=7 December 2011 }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Digital Preservation Award]]\n* [[Digital preservation]]\n* [[Data preservation]]\n* [[Preservation metadata]]\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.planets-project.eu/ Officiall website]\n* [https://cordis.europa.eu/programme/id/FP6-IST FP6-IST - Information Society Technologies]: thematic priority under the specific programme \"Integrating and strengthening the European research area\" (2002-2006). \n\n[[Category:FP6 projects]]\n[[Category:European Union and science and technology]]\n\n\n{{EU-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Digital preservation project}}\n{{Primary sources|Companies|date=April 2020}}\nThe '''Preservation and Long-term Access through Networked Services''' (PLANETS) project  addressed core digital preservation challenges. The primary goal for Planets was to build practical services and tools to help ensure long-term access to digital cultural and scientific assets. The outputs of this European project are, since 2010, sustained by the follow-on organisation, the Open Planets Foundation.<ref>{{cite web|title=Planets - Preservation and Long-term Access to our Cultural and Scientific Heritage. Fact Sheet (Record number:99184)|url=https://cordis.europa.eu/project/id/033789|website=cordis.europa.eu|language=en|date=11 April 2016|access-date=7 April 2020|publication-date=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title= Planets project |work= web site |year= 2009 |url= http://www.planets-project.eu/ |accessdate=7 December 2011 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title= The Open Planets Foundation |work= web site |year= 2010 |url= http://www.openplanetsfoundation.org/ |accessdate=7 December 2011 }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==See also==\n*[[Framework_Programmes_for_Research_and_Technological_Development#FP6_and_FP7|Sixth Framework Programme]]\n* [[Digital Preservation Award]]\n* [[Digital preservation]]\n* [[Data preservation]]\n* [[Preservation metadata]]\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.planets-project.eu/ Officiall website]\n* [https://cordis.europa.eu/programme/id/FP6-IST FP6-IST - Information Society Technologies]: thematic priority under the specific programme \"Integrating and strengthening the European research area\" (2002-2006). \n\n[[Category:FP6 projects]]\n[[Category:European Union and science and technology]]\n\n\n{{EU-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Calle Cool", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Preservation_and_Long-term_Access_through_Networked_Services"}
{"title_page": "Kamal Ahmed (singer)", "text_new": "{{More citations needed|date=March 2019}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name = Kamal Ahmed\n| background = solo_singer\n| image =Kamal Ahmed.jpg\n| caption = Ahmed in 2012\n| native_name = \u0995\u09be\u09ae\u09be\u09b2 \u0986\u09b9\u09ae\u09c7\u09a6 \n| native_name_lang = [[Bengali]]\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1965|09|09|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Pabna District|Pabna]], [[East Pakistan]], Pakistan\n| genre = [[Rabindra Sangeet]]\n| occupation = Singer, administrator\n| instrument =  Vocal, [[harmonium]], [[esraj]], violin, guitar\n| website = {{url|kamalahmedsinger.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Kamal Ahmed''' (born 9 September 1965)<ref>{{cite news|url=http://kamalahmedsinger.com/about/|title=Kamal Ahmed's 'Official Website'}}</ref> is a Bangladeshi [[Rabindra Sangeet]] (also known as Tagore songs) singer.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://shangetangon.com/?p=2208|script-title=bn:\u098f \u09b8\u09aa\u09cd\u09a4\u09be\u09b9\u09c7\u09b0 \u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09bf\u09af\u09bc \u09a4\u09be\u09b0\u0995\u09be \u2013 \u0995\u09be\u09ae\u09be\u09b2 \u0986\u09b9\u09ae\u09c7\u09a6|last=|first=|date=|work=|access-date=|via=|title=Archived copy|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190603093811/http://shangetangon.com/?p=2208|archive-date=2019-06-03|url-status=dead}}</ref> He is currently serving as the director of programme at [[Bangladesh Betar]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/arts-entertainment/music/news/we-have-move-forward-our-heritage-kamal-ahmed-1704907|title=\"We have to move forward, but with our heritage\" \u2013 Kamal Ahmed|date=2019-02-21|website=The Daily Star|language=en|access-date=2019-02-20}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.betar.gov.bd/site/page/d0f8e22c-d994-4bcc-bbc8-c95f4c62ac78/Official-Contact|title=Bangladesh Betar Directors List|last=|first=|date=|website=http|language=en|access-date=2019-06-30}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nAhmed was born in [[Pabna]] on 9 September 1965 to Kiam Uddin Biswas and Aziza Khatun. He has a son, Ahmed Rezwan Protik , and a daughter, Ahmed Rehnuma Prokriti.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://kamalahmedsinger.com/autobiography/|title=Autobiography|website=Kamal Ahmed(Singer)|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref>\n\n==Education==\nAfter passing HSC examinations from [[Pabna Edward College|Pabna Edward college]] in 1982, Ahmed got an opportunity to study soil science in [[Dhaka University]]. The chance to study at Dhaka was the turning point for him to be associated with [[Chhayanaut]], a cultural organization committed to build up music talents, especially those of Tagore singers. There he came closure to veteran Tagore singers like Wahidul Haque, Sanjida Khatun, Ikhtiar Omar, Serajus Salekin and others. He received lessons on classical music as well from Ustad Phool Mohammad. In his student life at Dhaka University, he was one of the members of Board of Directors of the DUCSU Cultural Team. He represented the cultural troops of DUCSU to perform Tagore songs at [[Kolkata University]] and [[Kalyani University]] in India in the 1980s. He was elected \"Cultural Secretary\" of Hall Union and won as the champion of cultural week of Shahidullah Hall, [[Dhaka University]].\n\n==Career==\n{{Excessive citations|section|date=April 2020}}\nAhmed is the former adviser of \"Rabindra Sangeet Shammilon Parishad\". Current he serves as Secretary General of the \"9th BCS Forum\".<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.theindependentbd.com/printversion/details/32922|title=9th BCS Forum gets new body| accessdate=2016-02-06 |publisher=The Independent}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thedailysangbad.com/entertainment/2016/02/10/49834|title=\u09ac\u09bf\u09b8\u09bf\u098f\u09b8 \u09ab\u09cb\u09b0\u09be\u09ae\u09c7\u09b0 \u09ae\u09b9\u09be\u09b8\u099a\u09bf\u09ac \u09b8\u0999\u09cd\u0997\u09c0\u09a4 \u09b6\u09bf\u09b2\u09cd\u09aa\u09c0 \u0995\u09be\u09ae\u09be\u09b2 \u0986\u09b9\u09ae\u09c7\u09a6| accessdate=2016-02-10 |publisher=\u09a6\u09c8\u09a8\u09bf\u0995 \u09b8\u0982\u09ac\u09be\u09a6}}</ref>\n\nPrior to beginning his career in the [[Bangladesh Civil Service]] (BCS), Ahmed opted for the information cadre as his first choice, although he could have joined the administrative cadre. He joined [[Bangladesh Betar]] in 1991. To date, he has worked over 26 years in Bangladesh Betar and 3 years in [[Bangladesh Television]]. Having a master's degree from Dhaka University and professional training in mass communication, mass communication research, networking and programme development for electronic mass media, he is the current Director (Program) of Bangladesh Betar.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hcidhaka.gov.in/igcc_data?id=eyJpdiI6ImVJRUxubzBwdUp6dm9RZ3Z5Y0c0Qmc9PSIsInZhbHVlIjoiNE5ITW1FV1ZuTmJ4M1lEaE81WmFMUT09IiwibWFjIjoiNWU5MmQyNWJmNzk1YTUyN2JmMjk1ZGM2YTExYzAyNjI4ODZhNzVkMmI2ZjQ3MmEwNjI3MTQ5NWExNDRiZjRiYiJ9|title=Welcome to High Commission of India, Bangladesh|website=www.hcidhaka.gov.in|access-date=2019-06-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.newagebd.net/article/75569/igcc-organises-barshar-bhalobasha|title=IGCC organises Barshar Bhalobasha|website=New Age {{!}} The Most Popular Outspoken English Daily in Bangladesh|language=en|access-date=2019-06-30}}</ref>{{Citation needed|date=March 2019}}\n\nMany of Ahmed's albums are based on Tagore songs, and besides performing on stage<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.daily-sun.com/printversion/details/400032|title=Kamal Ahmed mesmerises audience at Nat'l Museum|website=Daily Sun|language=en|access-date=2019-07-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/arts-entertainment/music/news/kamal-ahmed-and-shahina-lotas-duet-concert-1741453|title=Kamal Ahmed and Shahina Lota's duet concert|date=2019-05-10|website=The Daily Star|language=en|access-date=2019-07-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://edailyjanakantha.com/?d=2019-5-11&p=9|title=eJanakantha|website=edailyjanakantha.com|access-date=2019-07-05}}</ref> regularly on Bangladesh Betar and Bangladesh Television, and different other satellite TV channels in the country, he has performed Tagore songs in India,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/arts-entertainment/music/kamal-ahmed-wins-over-indian-tagore-aficionados-1355548|title=Kamal Ahmed wins over Indian Tagore aficionados\n| accessdate=2017-02-04|publisher=The Daily Star}}</ref> and Sri Lanka.\n\nAhmed performed Tagore Songs in [[India]], [[Sri Lanka]] & [[Canada]]. He also performed at the Indira Gandhi Cultural Centre Solo Program<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/arts-entertainment/music/news/kamal-ahmeds-borsha-o-bhalobasha-serenade-audiences-june-14-1755019|title=Kamal Ahmed\u2019s \u2018Borsha o Bhalobasha\u2019 to serenade audiences on June 14|date=2019-06-11|website=The Daily Star|language=en|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ittefaq.com.bd/print-edition/entertainment/63666/\u09ac\u09b0\u09cd\u09b7\u09be\u09b0-\u09ad\u09be\u09b2\u09cb\u09ac\u09be\u09b8\u09be-\u0986\u09af\u09bc\u09cb\u099c\u09bf\u09a4|title=\u2018\u09ac\u09b0\u09cd\u09b7\u09be\u09b0 \u09ad\u09be\u09b2\u09cb\u09ac\u09be\u09b8\u09be\u2019 \u0986\u09af\u09bc\u09cb\u099c\u09bf\u09a4 {{!}} \u09ac\u09bf\u09a8\u09cb\u09a6\u09a8 \u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09a4\u09bf\u09a6\u09bf\u09a8|website=ittefaq|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.daily-sun.com/printversion/details/400032/Kamal-Ahmed-mesmerises-audience-at-Nat\u2019l-Museum-|title=Kamal Ahmed mesmerises audience at Nat\u2019l Museum|website=Daily Sun|language=en|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/arts-entertainment/music/kamal-ahmed-performs-igcc-1389196|title=Kamal Ahmed performs at IGCC|last=|first=|date=2017-04-11|work=The Daily Star|access-date=2017-04-11|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.daily-sun.com/printversion/details/218743/Kamal-Ahmed-enthralls-audience-at-Nat%E2%80%99l-Museum-|title=Kamal Ahmed enthralls audience at Nat'l Museum|last=Sun|first=The Daily|date=|work=Kamal Ahmed enthralls audience at Nat'l Museum {{!}} daily-sun.com|access-date=2017-04-11|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.observerbd.com/details.php?id=68429|title=Kamal Ahmed mesmerises audience at IGCC|last=|first=|date=|website=www.observerbd.com|access-date=2017-04-11}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.theindependentbd.com/printversion/details/89600|title=Kamal Ahmed delights audience with Tagore song|last=Independent|first=The|date=|work=Kamal Ahmed delights audience with Tagore song {{!}} theindependentbd.com|access-date=2017-04-11}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://shangetangon.com/?p=3231|title=\u098f\u0995\u0995 \u09b8\u0999\u09cd\u0997\u09c0\u09a4 \u09b8\u09a8\u09cd\u09a7\u09cd\u09af\u09be \u0995\u09be\u09ae\u09be\u09b2 \u0986\u09b9\u09ae\u09c7\u09a6\u2026|last=|first=|date=2017-04-13|work=Shangetangon|access-date=2017-04-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170421125605/http://shangetangon.com/?p=3231|archive-date=2017-04-21|url-status=dead|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/multimedia/arts-entertainment/photo/borshaar-bhalobasha-1759450|title=Borshaar Bhalobasha|date=2019-06-19|website=The Daily Star|language=en|access-date=2019-07-09}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.observerbd.com/details.php?id=202821|title=Kamal Ahmed captivates Dhaka audience - Art & Culture - observerbd.com|website=The Daily Observer|access-date=2019-07-09}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://thedailynewnation.com/news/219031/kamal-ahmed-mesmerises-audience-at-natl-museum.html|title=Kamal Ahmed mesmerises audience at Nat'l Museum|last=Nation|first=The New|website=The New Nation|language=en|access-date=2019-07-16}}</ref>& the National Museum Solo Program<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/arts-entertainment/music/kamal-ahmed-perform-solo-musical-soiree-1444084|title=Kamal Ahmed to perform solo musical soiree|date=2017-08-06|work=The Daily Star|access-date=2018